# Changelog

## Unreleased

- Added depth-2 image API S3 uploader reports (frac-0049): `src/cypherclaw/image_api/s3_uploader.py` now exposes module-level `DEFAULT_CACHE_CONTROL`, `DEFAULT_CONTENT_TYPE`, and `CONTENT_TYPE_BY_EXTENSION` constants plus a frozen `UploadReport` dataclass and typed helpers `guess_content_type`, `categorize_upload_size`, `build_upload_report`, `summarize_upload`, and `summarize_upload_report` so worker batches and operator dashboards can map filenames to canonical MIME types, aggregate `UploadResult` records into bucket / object-count / total-bytes / keys / urls reports, classify byte sizes into empty/small/medium/large bands, and emit JSON-safe per-result and per-batch summaries. `upload_image` keeps its keyword-only signature, single `put_object` call, and direct-S3 URL contract; the cache-control header is now sourced from `DEFAULT_CACHE_CONTROL` rather than a literal. `tests/test_image_api_s3_uploader_depth.py` pins MIME classification (known + unknown + missing suffix), batch aggregation, empty-iterable handling, size-band thresholds, JSON-safe summaries, the cache-header contract, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_image_api_s3_uploader.py` remains the regression anchor for existing upload behavior, and `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` plus the startup identity tests remain green.

- Added depth-2 PromptClaw scaffold template reports (frac-0048): `promptclaw/templates.py` now exposes frozen `ScaffoldTemplateEntry` and `ScaffoldTemplateReport` dataclasses plus typed helpers `template_category`, `required_startup_prompt_paths`, `scaffold_template_entries`, `scaffold_template_report`, and `summarize_scaffold_templates` so callers can inspect generated starter scaffold files by category, byte size, required startup prompt coverage, and JSON-safe per-entry rows. Existing `project_scaffold(project_name)` output is preserved exactly for bootstrap and CLI init consumers. `tests/test_promptclaw_templates_depth.py` pins category classification, scaffold contract preservation, report totals/category counts, JSON-safe summaries, and fractal depth >= 2; bootstrap/config/orchestrator and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.

