+- Direct consumers reviewed: `src/cypherclaw/image_api/app.py`, `spec_parser.py`, `worker.py`, `gemini_backend.py`, `jobs_db.py`, `s3_uploader.py`, `__init__.py`, and `__main__.py`. Existing behavior is already wired end-to-end through FastAPI submission, YAML parsing, mocked Gemini generation, S3 upload, and SQLite job persistence.
+- Related tests reviewed: `tests/test_image_api_spec_parser.py`, `tests/test_image_api_worker.py`, `tests/test_image_api_app.py`, `tests/test_image_api_jobs_db.py`, `tests/test_image_api_s3_uploader.py`, and `tests/test_image_api_s3_uploader_depth.py`.
+- Fractal baseline: `sdp.fractal.classify_depth("src/cypherclaw/image_api/schemas.py")` reports depth 0 (`no functions found`). The simplest safe depth-2 path is to add typed JSON-safe schema summaries and profiles without changing the wire contract or runtime side effects.
